learning_outcomes.en:
Upon completion of the course a student will
*understand the importance of teaching culture in foreign language teaching;
*have a systematic overview of the formation of Britain and its history;
*have knowledge and understanding of different fields of life in modern Britain;
*understand and appreciate different cultures and cultural norms;
*be able to use different techniques and resources for teaching culture in English lessons at basic school;
*critically evaluate study materials; 
*have an overview of literature and websites related to teaching culture.
